---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy policy · Accessible.org"
  description="The privacy policy for this practice site. It is a static teaching site that does not collect personal data."
>
  <section class="lesson-head wrap">
    <p class="kicker">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The short version: this is a static teaching site that does not collect anything about you.
    </p>
    <p class="doc-meta">Last updated 23 June 2026</p>
  </section>

  <div class="wrap" style="padding-bottom: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing. This site has no accounts, no analytics, no advertising, and it sets no cookies.
        We do not track you across pages or sessions.
      </p>

      <h2>The forms in the lessons</h2>
      <p>
        The example pages include forms such as "Request invite" and controls such as the currency
        menu. These are demonstrations. They run entirely in your browser, do nothing when
        submitted, and send no data anywhere. Anything you type is never transmitted or stored.
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting and server logs</h2>
      <p>
        The site is served as static files through GitHub Pages. Like any web host, GitHub may
        process standard technical information, such as your IP address and the request, to deliver
        the page and keep it secure. That processing is covered by <a href="https://docs.github.com/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy statement</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        Pages here link to Accessible.org and occasionally to other sites. Those sites have their
        own privacy practices, which we do not control.
      </p>

      <h2>The parent organisation</h2>
      <p>
        This is a learning sub-site of <a href="https://accessible.org" rel="noopener">Accessible.org</a>.
        For the organisation's full privacy practices, or to ask a question, visit Accessible.org.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
